</asp:Content>

<asp:Content ID="Content3" ContentPlaceHolderID="For_Body_A" Runat="Server">

<p style="font-weight: bold;">Effective Date:  February 15th, 2017</p>

<p>Scantron Technology Solutions has created this Privacy Statement in order to demonstrate our commitment to privacy. The following discloses our information gathering and dissemination practices for our field technician’s mobile app: “ServiceCOMMAND Mobile” (the “App”). This Privacy Statement applies to all users of the App on or after the Effective Date (“Users”). Please read this Privacy Statement carefully. If you are not an employee of Scantron Technology Solutions, or if you do not agree to our practices, please do not use the App.</p>

<p>Please contact us if you have any questions or comments about our privacy practices or this Privacy Statement. You can reach us at the following address:</p>

<p>
Scantron Technology Solutions 
<br />ATTN:  Privacy Officer
<br />2020 South 156th Circle 
<br />Omaha, NE 68130
</p>

<p><asp:Label ID="Label1" runat="server" 
    Text="Collection of Information" 
    SkinID="labelTitleColor1_Small" /></p>

<p>Identity: The App requires Users to enter valid employee credentials.  Once authorized the User’s identity is used to retrieve, store and transmit enterprise data required in the course of the technician’s work.  The User’s employee and contact information is stored on the device.</p>

<p>Location: The App uses the device location to retrieve maps and driving information through an interface with Google Maps.</p>

<p>Photos, Media and Files:  The app has an audio module to associate stored sounds with App events.  Sounds can be customized, which allows selection from stored audio files on the device.</p>

<p>Phone: The app allows the User to click displayed phone numbers and access the device's phone.</p>

<p>Microphone: The app makes use of the device microphone to allow spoken words to be converted to text and stored in the App database.</p>

<p>Camera and Flash: The app makes use of the device camera to read traditional and QR Barcodes.  This barcode reader also accesses the camera's light if needed during scanning.</p>

<p>Push Notification: The app utilizes Google Cloud Messaging (GCM) to enable the app to listen for and receive push notification of business data.  Push notification uses the GET_ACCOUNTS permission which requires the User to enter their credentials for programmatic access to an active Google user account.</p>

<p>Stored Data: The data on the device is stored in an encrypted manner.  It is unencrypted only at the point the data is used or displayed.  The data stored is only used to support the work of the technician on behalf of Scantron Technology Solutions.   We do not sell or disseminate the App’s data to anyone outside our company except as explained below. </p>

<p><asp:Label ID="Label2" runat="server" 
    Text="Disclosure to Third Parties" 
    SkinID="labelTitleColor1_Small" /></p>

<p>We will not disclose any User contact information to third parties except to:</p>
<ul class="ulDefault">
    <li>Affiliated companies (e.g., subsidiaries and other companies owned by or controlled by Harland Clarke Holdings Corporation) who may only use the information for the purposes described above.</li>
    <li>Our service providers that provide services for us such as sending emails on our behalf and processing payments.</li>
    <li>Effect a merger, acquisition, or otherwise; to support the sale or transfer of business assets; to enforce our rights or protect our property; to protect the rights, property or safety of others, investigate fraud, respond to a government request; or as needed to support auditing, compliance and corporate governance functions. </li>
</ul>

<p><asp:Label ID="Label3" runat="server" 
    Text="Website Links and Social Media " 
    SkinID="labelTitleColor1_Small" /></p>

<p>The App contains links to websites and to social media (such as Facebook and Twitter). We are not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of such other websites, social media, chat rooms, forums, message boards and/or news groups which are linked to or from our App. Please remember that any information that is disclosed in these areas may become public information and you should exercise caution when deciding to disclose your personal information on these websites. This Privacy Statement only applies to the use of this App.</p>

<p><asp:Label ID="Label4" runat="server" 
    Text="Security" 
    SkinID="labelTitleColor1_Small" /></p>

<p>The App has security measures in place to protect from loss, misuse and alteration of the information under our control.</p>

<p><asp:Label ID="Label5" runat="server" 
    Text="Notice to Residents of Countries outside the United States of America" 
    SkinID="labelTitleColor1_Small" /></p>

<p>Scantron Technology Solutions is headquartered in the United States of America. Information may be accessed by us or transferred to us in the United States or to our affiliates or service providers elsewhere in the world. By providing us with information, you consent to this transfer. We will protect the privacy and security of this information according to this Privacy Statement, regardless of where it is processed or stored.</p>

<p><asp:Label ID="Label6" runat="server" 
    Text="Changes to this Privacy Statement" 
    SkinID="labelTitleColor1_Small" /></p>

<p>From time to time, we may update this Privacy Statement to clarify our practices or to reflect new or different privacy practices, such as when we add new features to our App. We encourage you to periodically review this page for the latest information about our privacy practices.</p>

